article.headline: Tennessee St. 87, SE Missouri 75
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Bruce Price had 33 points, Gerald Robinson Jr. scored 18 and Tennessee State beat Southeast Missouri State 87-75 on Thursday night. Jerrell Houston added 12 points for the Tigers (7-10, 4-4 Ohio Valley Conference), who led by just a point at the half. The Redhawks (11-8, 6-3 OVC) were led by Kenard Moore's 16 points. Marcus Rhodes and Jaycen Herring scored 11 points apiece for Southeast Missouri State, which shot just 7-for-23 from 3-point range.
